ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC STEPDISC <options> ; 
      CLASS variable ; 
      BY variables ; 
      FREQ variable ; 
      VAR variables ; 
      WEIGHT variable ; 

Given a classification variable and several quantitative variables, the STEPDISC procedure 
performs a stepwise discriminant analysis to select a subset of the quantitative variables 
for use in discriminating among the classes.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: CLASS variable ;

The values of the CLASS variable define the groups for analysis. Class levels are determined by 
the formatted values of the CLASS variable. The CLASS variable can be numeric or character.
